result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
10:00 AM Prosecuting attorney Natalia Gess in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Cici B. Antone in court, in custody.  Attorney Leonie Dolch in court for Cici B. Antone.  Court states cases and appearances.  State notes they are in compliance w/victim rights.  Restitution requested in 21CM90 and 21CF657 - stips filed.  Atty Dolch and DE are in agreement.  Court notes cash bond not forfeited will be applied to restitution amounts ordered.  Parties in agreement.  Atty Dolch enters NC pleas to agreed charges.  DE also pleads NC.  Court questions DE on pleas then notes there have not been prelim waivers in 2 of the CF cases.  Recess for Atty Dolch to review waiver of prelims and State to prepare the informations in those 2 cases.  Back on the record, the Court questions DE re: his right to a prelim in 21CF657 and 22CF258.  DE waives that right.  Court accepts the DE's waiver of right to prelim/finds probable cause/binds DE over.  Atty Dolch stands mute to all charges in 21CF657 and 22CF258.  Court enters NG pleas and continues questioning DE on her pleas/accepts/finds DE guilty to the agreed counts.  State makes statement on behalf of the joint recommendations.  Atty Dolch makes statement on behalf of the DE.  DE has nothing to add.  Court advises DE re: voting rights and felony firearms warnings. 
 Court admonishes DE and sentences.  Atty Dolch will reach out to P&P today and let them know that the DE will be going to other counties as there are other warrants.
